    • Constructor Detail

      • GenRDotJavaStep

        public GenRDotJavaStep(Set<Path> resDirectories,
               Path genDirectoryPath,
               String libraryPackage,
               boolean isTempRDotJava,
               Set<String> extraLibraryPackages,
               Optional<Path> aaptOverride)
        Creates a command that will run aapt for the purpose of generating R.java. Additionally, this command will generate the corresponding R.txt file.
        Parameters:
        resDirectories - Directories of resource files. Will be specified with -S to aapt
        genDirectoryPath - Directory where R.java and potentially R.txt will be generated
        libraryPackage - Normally, aapt expects an AndroidManifest.xml so that it can extract the package attribute to determine the Java package of the generated R.java file. For this class, the client must specify the package directly rather than the path to AndroidManifest.xml. This precludes the need to keep a number of dummy AndroidManifest.xml files in the codebase.
        isTempRDotJava - If true, the values of the resource values in the generated R.java will be meaningless.

        If false, this command will produce an R.java file with resource values designed to match those in an .apk that includes the resources.

        extraLibraryPackages -
        aaptOverride -
